Terrorists in large numbers have reportedly blocked the Kaduna-Abuja road. This is happening four days after an Abuja-Kaduna Train was bombed and about wight passengers killed while many others were abducted by terrorists.  Senator Shehu Sani disclosed this on his verified Twitter handle on Thursday afternoon. He said, “Just got a distress call that bandits in large numbers have again blocked the Kaduna-Abuja road this afternoon. Travellers are speedily turning backward.” Details Later…